iOS app
  |__"'How to Use App' Video"/introduction.mov

introduction.mov is exported from OpenShot 1.4.3 on Ubuntu 17.10
Target: MOV (h.264)
Video Profile: iOS_profile


Export NEW introduction.mov
---------------------------

(1) install OpenShot

Ubuntu: (terminal) $ sudo apt install openshot
macOS: https://github.com/OpenShot/openshot-qt/releases/download/v2.4.1/OpenShot-v2.4.1-x86_64.dmg


(2) install iOS_profile

...open a terminal

Ubuntu: $ cp iOS_profile ~/.openshot/user_profiles/
macOS: $ cp iOS_profile ~/.openshot_qt/profiles/


(3) extract introduction.tar.gz, and set permissions

$ sudo mkdir /usr/local/introduction
$ sudo tar -xzf introduction.tar.gz -C /usr/local/introduction
$ sudo chmod -R o+w /usr/local/introduction


(4) open the project

$ cd /usr/local/introduction

Ubuntu: $ openshot Default\ Project.osp
macOS: open .. > drag "introduction" directory onto sidebar
macOS: (back to terminal) $ open -a "OpenShot Video Editor" > Open Project > "introduction" directory from sidebar > Default\ Project.osp


(5) export NEW introduction.mov

File > Export Video...

File Name: introduction.mov
Target: MOV (h.264)
Video Profile: iOS_profile

Export Video


(6) OPTIONAL: Replace original archive, and clean up

(back to terminal) $ sudo tar -czf /path/to/introduction.tar.gz *
$ sudo rm -r /usr/local/introduction


Notes
-----
(1) video clips and images may render differently between Ubuntu and macOS, due to differences between GTK+ and Qt
(2) researcher recorded videos in Open Broadcaster Software (OBS), hence the "obs" directory in /usr/local/introduction